message.body: @bainezy94 Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input).

fragments.text: @bainezy94 Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input).

message.body: Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used AT THE SAME TIME, NOT ONE

fragments.text: Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used AT THE SAME TIME, NOT ONE

message.body: AFTER ANOTHER: b+up+right. You can't use opposite commands at the same time: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop

message.body: @taumanplays Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input).

fragments.text: @taumanplays Valid inputs are A, B, Z, L, R, Start, CUp, CDown, CLeft, CRight (C buttons), DUp, DDown, DLeft, DRight (D-Pad, unused in most games), Up, Down, Left and Right (Analog stick, used in almost every game as the standard movement input).

message.body: Typos work too! Directions can be replaced with cardinal directions: N, S, W, E, North, South, West, East, this works for C buttons and D-Pad too. ex: CN, CNorth, DS, DSouth, etc. Up to 3 DIFFERENT commands can be used AT THE SAME TIME, NOT ONE

message.body: AFTER ANOTHER: b+up+right. You can't use opposite commands at the same time: Left+Right, Up+Down, etc., WILL NOT WORK. End your input with - to hold down indefinitely until the next input comes: a+z+right-. Alternatively, you can type Wait or Stop
